What I learned about this particular attack is that it violates trust within Windows RDP. 

Running nmap led me to 3389/tcp open ms-wbt-server Microsoft Terminal Services

The reason this port is special is because of ms-wbt-server; this gave me my in. 

Next was XFree RDP to remotely connect to their system. 

The biggest takeaway is how easy it is to manipulate the trust process. 

I dont mean easy as the human definition. A curious, determined mind on any level will find a way. 

There is no stopping a man or machine that is determined. 

Determination can take a complex design and make it look simple. 
